<subSubSection id="B291B68B9E53FF836DBAFE913628C683" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FA34E5009E53FF836DBAFE913628C683" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="C8FF39129E53FF836DBAFE913200C64B" bold="true" box="[199,314,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Small species of uniform dark brownish grey, almost black, glossy appearance. The species does not resemble any other known Afrotropical species, either in habitus or in the structure of the male genitalia, characterized by the glomerulus shape of the ventral part of the valvula and by the two long parallel rows of cornuti.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B291B68B9E53FF836DBAFE6D305BC4E7" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="description">
<paragraph id="FA34E5009E53FF836DBAFE6D32D8C54F" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="C8FF39129E53FF836DBAFE6D326BC6FF" bold="true" box="[199,337,439,465]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Description</emphasis>
. Wingspan 
<quantity id="3D7348E59E53FF836CABFE6D3123C6FC" box="[470,537,439,466]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
. Head dark brownish grey. Antenna: scape without erect scales, flagellum ringed brown and light ochre. Labial palpus brownish grey, second segment lighter on the ventral side, about 1.5 times as long as the third. Proboscis short, of normal shape. Thorax and tegula dark brownish grey. Forewing of uniform dark brownish grey with fringes of same colour. Hindwing and fringes dark brownish grey.Abdomen of same colour. The whole insect is slightly shiny.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA34E5009E53FF836DBAFDB132BFC5E3" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
Abdominal structures (
<figureCitation id="62B0F9859E53FF836CACFDB13113C5AB" box="[465,553,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–14" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox="[259,1304,547,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-146@3.[259,1329,525,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11–14. Male genitalia of C. kibalensis Baldizzone, sp. nov. 11, GP Bldz 17167, holotype. 12, enlarged detail of valva and phallotheca. 13, enlarged detail of cornuti. 14, abdominal segments 1-6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524217" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524217/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
): No posterior lateral struts, transverse strut, curved in middle with thinner proximal edge and thicker distal edge. Tergal disks (3rd tergite) about 5 times longer than wide, covered with about 18-24 conical spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA34E5009E53FF836DBAFD0D3788C4AC" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="62B0F9859E53FF836C03FD0D3130C5DF" box="[382,522,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–14" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox="[259,1304,547,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-146@3.[259,1329,525,1951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11–14. Male genitalia of C. kibalensis Baldizzone, sp. nov. 11, GP Bldz 17167, holotype. 12, enlarged detail of valva and phallotheca. 13, enlarged detail of cornuti. 14, abdominal segments 1-6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524217" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524217/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Figs. 11–13</figureCitation>
): Gnathos knob globular. Tegumen broad, truncate-conical; pedunculus slightly expanded externally. Transtilla long, thin, linear. Valvula small, elongated in ventral area ending in shape of a glomerulus. Cucullus squat, slightly curved, more sclerotized in dorsal part. Sacculus narrow, dorsal angle with thin triangular protuberance, curved and rounded at apex. Phallotheca conical, more sclerotized in ventral part. Cornuti very numerous, shaped like short spines, arranged in two elongated, curved and parallel rows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA34E5009E53FF836DBAFC51313CC48B" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1042]" box="[199,518,907,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Female genitalia: Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA34E5009E53FF836DBAFC75305BC4E7" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1042]" box="[199,865,943,970]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="C8FF39129E53FF836DBAFC753208C4E7" bold="true" box="[199,306,943,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Bionomy</emphasis>
. The early stages and the foodplant are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
