<subSubSection id="B291B68B9E53FF836DBAFC2D3649C33F" box="[199,1395,1015,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FA34E5009E53FF836DBAFC2D3649C33F" blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1042]" box="[199,1395,1015,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="C8FF39129E53FF836DBAFC2D3272C33F" bold="true" box="[199,328,1015,1041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name derives from that of 
<collectingRegion id="384F2BE29E53FF836FCCFC2D31C6C33F" box="[689,764,1015,1041]" country="Uganda" name="Kibale" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Kibale</collectingRegion>
National Park (fig. 29) where the species was collected.
</paragraph>
